Rating: 3
I served this to my in-laws, who were very impressed with how such simple ingredients could yield such a great salad. I only marinated the beans in the dressing for an hour, and I don't think they really picked up much of its flavor, so I recommend a generous amount of time to soak the veggies. I used those grape tomatoes that I seem to be seeing everywhere these days in lieu of the cherry tomatoes, and probably would stick to the original recipe next time. The grape tomatoes were more expensive and in my opinion don't need a dressing on them. They're good and sweet to eat on their own, and the cherry tomatoes would have gotten the job done. I also may add another tablespoonful of basil next time. This really was a super side dish to our barbecued chicken and the Sweet Corn and Basmati Rice Salad, which is also terrific. Between those two dishes, my mother in law left with my June copy of the magazine! I guess that's what websites are for!

